article.headline: Green Bay 80, Houston Baptist 78
article.story: HOUSTON -- Mike Schachtner scored two free throws with six seconds left to help Green Bay defeat Houston Baptist 80-78 on Monday night. Ryan Tillema led Green Bay (8-4) with 24 points and was 8-of-11 from the field. Rahmon Fletcher added 18 and Schachtner had 13. Randy Berry had 11 rebounds. Gordon Watt scored 25 points with seven rebounds for Houston Baptist (0-12) and was 11-of-18 from the field. Emanuel Willis scored 15 points. Baron Sauls added 12 points and Andrew Puzyk contributed 11 points. Green Bay led 37-28 at the half.
